  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DELT4SLOG III</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For the proposed 2014/2015 intervention under the Deepening Expenditure Line Tracking for States &lt;(&gt;&amp;&lt;)&gt; LGAs in the Niger Delta, DELT4SLOG III, there will be capacity building of the civil society on budgeting, advocacy, monitoring, town hall meetings for grassroots mobilization and dissemination of budget information etc and tracking of the 2013 budgets of selected states, LGAs and agencies.

At another level, it is expected that the impacts being made will be consolidated through applying learning and challenges to make desired improvements. The scenario is that the existing structure or platform mentioned above will be supported to drive a collaborative linkages with the states and LGAs using the data generated from DELT4SLOG I and II to create awareness among other findings on the scattered abandoned projects in the region while simultaneously seeking remediation,  also lobby for the people to participatein budgetary processes in their LGAs through using the traditional rulers etc to pay continual advocacy visits to the target authorities to request for their community needs.

The Desk Review data on abandoned and haphazardly implemented projects will be simplified and shared to participants during these Town hall meetings. This will empower citizens with information for active participation in governance. It is envisaged thatwhere possible the traditional rulers can accompany the budget monitors for the advocacy visits and the budget monitors can also pay advocacy visits to the traditional rulers where necessary. Such advocacy visits will also  be tothe accountability institutions in the states like the public procurement office, Fiscal Responsibility Commission, Ministry of finance and Economic Planning, State House of Assemblies, LGAs, Traditional Rulers, etc</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="90">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Niger Delta Budget Monitoring Group (NDEBUMOG)</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Niger Delta Budget Monitoring Group, NDEBUMOG is a regional non- governmental organization formed in 2005, and works in the areas of budget advocacy, transparency, accountability and anti-corruption in the Niger Delta and Nigeria in general. It has the mission to promote transparency and accountability in the public resource management through pro-poor budgeting and anti-corruption in theNiger Delta and democratic consolidation in Nigeria. Novib and NDEBUMOG started collaborating in 2011 to support small initiative of Deepening Expenditure Line Tracking of States and LGAs within the Niger Delta focusing on mobilizing citizens and building capacity for the expenditure tracking using participatory approaches.

Following the success of the DELT4SLOG1, as reported in the 2012 Narrative report and observed by the toolbox team in March 2013, Oxfam Novib decided to support the planned DELT4SLOG 2 to deepen the achieved outcomes of the project in 2012.   The project aims to gather useful budget data for advocacy through desk review and field budget tracking of capital projects in the selected locations, strengthen the capacity of CSOs, NDEBUMOG staff, Journalists and community representatives on budget tracking, and established platforms of engagement in Rivers, Bayelsa and Delta States to hold governments accountable on its stewardship through dialogue with the Legislatures and other government representatives.</narrative>
  </participating-org>
